rs%2C%202.3%20million%20people%20find%20themselves%20in%20an%20open%20air%20prison%20in%20Gaza%20confronting%20degradation%2C%20anguish%2C%20dispossession%2C%20and%20political%20oppression.%20They%20remain%20afraid%20for%20their%20lives%20not%20knowing%20when%20Israel%20will%20bombard%20their%20spaces%20and%20ruthlessly%20kill%2C%20maim%2C%20and%20mutilate%20people%20in%20thousands%20with%20impunity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20international%20community%20generally%20watches%20muted%20%E2%80%93%20indifferent%20to%20their%20plight.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20number%20of%20victims%20multiplies%20with%20each%20passing%20day.%20In%20Gaza%2C%20children%2C%20women%2C%20elderly%2C%20young%20people%20who%20dream%20of%20a%20future%20when%20they%20can%20work%20in%20decent%20jobs%2C%20lie%20sick%20and%20grievously%20injured%20by%20the%20indiscriminate%20and%20persistent%20bombings%20on%20civilian%20populations.%20The%20population%20as%20a%20whole%20is%20deliberately%20deprived%20of%20food%20and%20medicines%20by%20the%20Israeli%20blockade%20in%20Gaza.%20In%20short%2C%20Gaza%20is%20nothing%20less%20than%20a%20concentration%20camp%20and%20one%20that%20is%20comparable%20to%20the%20worst%20in%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20little%20boy%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20illustrates%20the%20shock%20and%20awe%20of%20living%20like%20this.%20He%20recites%20how%2C%20one%20morning%2C%20he%20left%20his%20home%20to%20go%20to%20the%20sea-shore%20where%20rations%20are%20distributed%20to%20refugees%2C%20homeless%20and%20the%20jobless.%20That%20morning%2C%20as%20usual%2C%20he%20was%20up%20at%205%20am%20on%20his%20way%20to%20the%20beach%20where%20food%20was%20distributed.%20It%20was%20a%20must-do%20ritual%2C%20for%20else%20his%20family%20would%20go%20hungry%20for%20the%20day.%20He%20set%20out%20to%20return%20home%20with%20a%20skip%20and%20smile%2C%20assured%20he%20had%20done%20his%20duty%20towards%20his%20old%20grandparents%