aradise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey're%20under-appreciated%20at%20work%2C%20violence%20is%20too%20high%2C%20and%20foreign-born%20women%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20problems%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20see%20is%20not%20gender%20equality%2C'%26quot%3B%20%C3%81sa%20Steinars%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20surprisingly%20sunny%20day%20in%20late%20October%2C%20an%20estimated%20100%2C000%20women%20and%20non-binary%20people%20%E2%80%94%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20country's%20population%20%E2%80%94%20gathered%20in%20the%20centers%20of%20cities%2C%20towns%2C%20and%20villages%20across%20Iceland%20as%20part%20of%20a%2024-hour%20strike%2C%20where%20they%20ditched%20work%20and%20household%20chores.%20Instead%2C%20they%20protested%20around%20the%20theme%20of%20%26quot%3BKallar%C3%B0u%20%C3%BEetta%20jafnr%C3%A9tti%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BYou%20call%20this%20equality%3F%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Reykjavik%2C%20the%20Icelandic%20capital%2C%20the%20biggest%20gathering%20was%20held%20by%20far.%20Speakers%20took%20to%20the%20stage%20to%20demand%20equal%20pay%2C%20address%20gender-based%20violence%2C%20and%20call%20for%20more%20respect%20for%20women%20and%20non-binary%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20country's%20prime%20minister%20took%20the%20day%20off%20work%20to%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20incredible%2C%26quot%3B%20Saga%20L%C3%ADf%20Fri%C3%B0riksd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Viking%20Women%2C%20an%20Icelandic%20women-only%20tour%20company%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20chills%20all%20over%20while%20standing%20there.%20It%20was%20a%20beautiful%20moment%20being%20downtown%20with%20almost%20100%2C000%20women%2C%20and%20we%20were%20all%20chanting%20and%20clapping%20and%20raising%20our%20fists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20across%20Iceland%20gather%20during%20the%20women's%20strike%20in%20Reykjavik%2C%20Iceland%2C%20Tuesday%2C%20Oct.%2024%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65772b7c0ec98e92f74e123d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224096%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpeakers%20at%20the%20strike%20demanded%20equal%20pay%2C%20addressed%20gender-based%20violence%2C%20and%20called%20for%20more%20respect%20for%20women%20and%20non-binary%20people.%3Cp%3EArni%20Torfason%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIceland%20is%20widely%20seen%20through%20rose-tinted%20glasses%20as%20a%20gender%20equality%20paradise.%20It%20has%20topped%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum's%20global%20gender%20gap%20index%20for%2014%20years%20in%20a%20row%2C%20and%20the%20ranking%20claims%20the%20country%20has%20closed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F06%2Fglobal-gender-gap-parity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E91.2%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20gender%20gap%2C%20which%20it%20defines%20as%20the%20difference%20in%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20economic%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20men%2C%20women%2C%20and%20non-binary%20people%20still%20aren't%20equal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIceland%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20yet%20at%20parity%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20number%20one%20in%20the%20world%20and%20despite%20many%2C%20many%20years%20of%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20Saadia%20Zahidi%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20WEF%2C%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fwatch%2F%3Fv%3D1251077192104312%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evideo%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Icelandic%20and%20foreign-born%20women%20told%20BI%20that%20though%20they%20largely%20feel%20safe%20in%20Iceland%2C%20it's%20no%20feminist%20paradise.%20The%20country%20can't%20become%20complacent%20and%20let%20progress%20stagnate%20by%20relying%20on%20its%20status%20secured%20by%20rankings%20such%20as%20the%20WEF's%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20talk%20about%20Iceland%20as%20this%20kind%20of%20utopia%20and%20we%20have%20come%20a%20long%20way%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20feminism%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20inclusivity%20and%20diversity%2C%20but%20we%20are%20not%20near%20where%20we%20need%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Valenttina%20Griffin%2C%20co-founder%20of%20the%20non-profit%20WomenTechIceland%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20far%20away%20from%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20delivered%20the%20message%20that%20we%20are%20the%20most%20gender%20equal%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20but%20sometimes%20living%20here%20you%20are%20like%2C%20'how%20can%20we%20be%20the%20best%20country%20in%20the%20world%3F%2C'%26quot%3B%20%C3%81sa%20Steinars%2C%20a%20photographer%20and%20adventure%20content%20creator%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20what%20I%20see%20is%20not%20gender%20equality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Words%20painted%20onto%20the%20wall%20of%20a%20building%20in%20Iceland%2C%20including%20information%20about%20the%20first%20women's%20rights%20gatherings%20in%20the%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65730ab40ec98e92f74d6a1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223468%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGraffiti%20spotted%20on%20a%20building%20in%20Reykjavik%20says%20in%20Icelandic%20that%20women%20don't%20yet%20have%20complete%20freedom.%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIceland's%20recent%20women%20and%20non-binary%20people's%20strike%2C%20held%20on%20October%2024%2C%20has%20its%20origins%20in%20the%20country's%20Red%20Stockings%20movement.%20Though%20the%20Icelandic%20Women's%20Rights%20Association%20was%20founded%20back%20in%201907%2C%20it%20wasn't%20until%201970%20that%20the%20campaign%20for%20gender%20equality%20really%20began%20to%20boom%20in%20the%20Nordic%20country%2C%20when%20the%20Red%20Stockings%20movement%20came%20to%20the%20scene%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20sort%20of%20colorful%20bang%2C%26quot%3B%20Rakel%20Adolphsd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20archivist%20at%20the%20country's%20Women's%20History%20Archives%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20of%20mainly%20young%20women%2C%20influenced%20by%20feminist%20movements%20in%20Denmark%20and%20the%20US%2C%20staged%20radical%20performances%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flandsbokasafn.is%2Findex.php%3Fmact%3DNews%2Ccntnt01%2Cdetail%2C0%26cntnt01articleid%3D1711%26cntnt01origid%3D1%26cntnt01detailtemplate%3DLBS_KjorgripurDetail%26cntnt01returnid%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecrowning%20a%20cow%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BMiss%20Young%20Iceland%26quot%3B%20at%20a%20beauty%20contest%20in%201972.%20It%20also%20held%20conferences%20where%20women%20could%20speak%20publicly%20about%20wages%20and%20workers'%20rights%20without%20being%20taken%20over%20by%20men%2C%20Adolphsd%C3%B3ttir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Red%20Stockings%20decided%20in%201975%20to%20hold%20the%20country's%20first%20women's%20strike%20%E2%80%94%20later%20renamed%20Women's%20Day%20Off%20to%20avoid%20some%20backlash%20%E2%80%94%20on%20United%20Nations'%20Day%2C%20campaigning%20primarily%20for%20equal%20pay%20and%20job%20opportunities.%20On%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkvennasogusafn.is%2Findex.php%3Fpage%3Dwomens-day-off-1975%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eflyers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20organizers%20pointed%20out%20women's%20lack%20of%20trade%20union%20representation%20and%20inability%20to%20become%20full%20members%20of%20the%20Farmers'%20Union%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20under-appreciation%20of%20their%20housework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20estimated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkvennasogusafn.is%2Findex.php%3Fmact%3DNews%2Ccntnt01%2Cdetail%2C0%26cntnt01articleid%3D325%26cntnt01origid%3D36%26cntnt01detailtemplate%3DNews_events%26cntnt01returnid%3D48%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E90%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Icelandic%20women%20took%20part%2C%20stopping%20both%20paid%20and%20unpaid%20work%20for%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20like%20a%20wake%20up%20call%20for%20many%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20Thorgerdur%20J.%20Einarsd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20professor%20of%20gender%20studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Iceland%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20off%20helped%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20the%201980%20election%20of%20Vigd%C3%ADs%20Finnbogad%C3%B3ttir%2C%20the%20world's%20first%20democratically-elected%20female%20president%2C%20and%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20political%20party%20made%20up%20only%20of%20women.%20It%20also%20led%20to%20a%20number%20of%20further%2C%20smaller%20women's%20strikes.%20But%202023%20was%20the%20biggest%20strike%20since%201975.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAwareness%20of%20gender%20inequality%20increased%20following%20the%20financial%20crisis%20of%202008%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bunraveled%20the%20masculine%20undertones%20in%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Einarsd%C3%B3ttir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20this%20Icelandic%20Viking%20discourse%20that%20they%20were%20very%20good%2C%20smart%20businessmen%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20economy%20just%20collapsed%20overnight.%20And%20then%20we%20had%20a%20very%20strong%20discourse%20on%3A%20'Now%20when%20the%20men%20have%20run%20the%20economy%20into%20ruins%2C%20it's%20women's%20turn.'%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2009%2Ffeb%2F22%2Ficeland-women%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWomen%20were%20appointed%20to%20positions%20of%20leadership%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20country%20got%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icelandreview.com%2Fnews%2Ffirst-female-bishop-elected-iceland%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efirst%20female%20bishop%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20female%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Icelandic%20Prime%20minister%20J%C3%B3hanna%20Sigur%C3%B0ard%C3%B3ttir%20is%20pictured%20on%20February%201%2C%202009%20on%20her%20arrival%20in%20Reykjavik.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657304bc0ec98e92f74d68d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222832%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJ%C3%B3hanna%20Sigur%C3%B0ard%C3%B3ttir%20was%20elected%20in%202009%2C%20becoming%20Iceland's%20first%20female%20prime%20minister%20and%20the%20world's%20first%20openly%20gay%20leader.%3Cp%3EHalldor%20Kolbeins%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20gender%20equality%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrapevine.is%2Fnews%2F2020%2F04%2F22%2Fkatrin-jakobsdottir-highlights-covid-19-gender-equality-concerns%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emounted%20again%20during%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd.org%2Fcoronavirus%2Fpolicy-responses%2Fcaregiving-in-crisis-gender-inequality-in-paid-and-unpaid-work-during-covid-19-3555d164%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20took%20on%20more%20childcare%20responsibilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20reported%20instances%20of%20violence%20against%20women%20rose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESonja%20%C3%9Dr%20%C3%9Eorbergsd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20BSRB%2C%20the%20Icelandic%20federation%20of%20public%20sector%20unions%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20organizers%20of%20this%20year's%20strike.%20She%20told%20BI%20that%20Icelandic%20women's%20groups%2C%20LGBTQ%2B%20organizations%2C%20and%20unions%20decided%20to%20hold%20the%20strike%20because%20of%20a%20backlash%20to%20gender%20equality%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupport%20for%20the%20strike%20was%20unanimous%2C%20%C3%9Eorbergsd%C3%B3ttir%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20question%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%20Most%20companies%20were%20also%20cooperative%20and%20agreed%20to%20still%20pay%20their%20workers%20who%20went%20on%20strike%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strike's%20objective%20was%20to%20show%20what%20happens%20when%20women%20and%20non-binary%20people%20stop%20working%2C%20she%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20effect%20should%20be%20that%20Iceland%20stops%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20what%20we%20want%20to%20show.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20number%20of%20schools%2C%20kindergartens%2C%20and%20shops%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ficelandic-women-24-hour-strike-over-inequality-2023-10-24%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eclosed%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20the%20shortage%20of%20workers%2C%20while%20some%20hospitals%20stopped%20non-emergency%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20also%20sent%20out%20quite%20a%20direct%20message%20to%20men%20saying%20that%20this%20was%20the%20day%20that%20their%20spouses%20or%20the%20women%20or%20the%20non-binary%20people%20in%20their%20lives%20were%20going%20to%20strike%2C%26quot%3B%20%C3%9Eorbergsd%C3%B3ttir%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20this%20was%20the%20day%20that%20they%20had%20to%20take%20all%20the%20responsibility%20of%20children%20and%20the%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year's%20strike%20aimed%20%26quot%3Bto%20provoke%20this%20image%20of%20us%20being%20an%20equal%20rights%20paradise%20because%20we%20don't%20feel%20that%20people%20can%20connect%20to%20that%20in%20daily%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20%C3%9Eorbergsd%C3%B3ttir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInclusivity%20was%20a%20key%20part%20of%20this%20year's%20strike.%20The%20event%20was%20rebranded%20as%20a%20strike%20for%20women%20and%20non-binary%20people%2C%20and%20%C3%9Eorbergsd%C3%B3ttir%20told%20BI%20that%20it%20meant%20many%20people%20learned%20the%20Icelandic%20word%20for%20non-binary%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttendees%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20were%20impressed%20by%20the%20broad%20range%20of%20speakers%20at%20the%20Reykjavik%20event%2C%20too.%20Alice%20Olivia%20Clarke%2C%20who%20relocated%20from%20Canada%20to%20Iceland%2030%20years%20ago%2C%20addressed%20the%20audience%20in%20both%20Icelandic%20and%20English.%20Speaking%20at%20the%20event%20was%20%26quot%3Bsuch%20a%20privilege%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGender-equality%20rankings%20don't%20reflect%20everyday%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFactors%20that%20helped%20secure%20Iceland's%20position%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20WEF's%20gender-equality%20ranking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F06%2Fglobal-gender-gap-parity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einclude%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20subsidized%20childcare%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20leadership%20roles%20and%20STEM%20professions%2C%20and%20women's%20educational%20attainment.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fpublications%2Fglobal-gender-gap-report-2023%2Fin-full%2Fbenchmarking-gender-gaps-2023%2F%23country-coverage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWEF%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20points%20out%20legislation%20that%20requires%20companies%20with%20more%20than%2025%20employees%20to%20show%20they%20pay%20equal%20wages%2C%20entitles%20both%20parents%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vinnumalastofnun.is%2Fen%2Fmaternitypaternity-leave-fund%2Fmaternitypaternity-leave%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esix%20months%20of%20parental%20leave%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20requires%20women%20to%20make%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statice.is%2Fpublications%2Fnews-archive%2Fenterprises%2Fboards-of-directors%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebetween%2040%25%20and%2060%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20board%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIceland%20also%20tops%20the%20WEF's%20political%20empowerment%20subindex%2C%20with%20a%20parity%20score%20of%2090.1%25%20compared%20to%20the%20global%20average%20of%2022.1%25.%20At%20the%20country's%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.althingi.is%2Fenglish%2Fmembers-of-parliament%2Fpolitical-parties%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egeneral%20election%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%2C%2030%20women%20and%2033%20men%20were%20voted%20into%20the%20Al%C3%BEingi%2C%20the%20Icelandic%20parliament%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.government.is%2Fgovernment%2Fcurrent-government%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehalf%20of%20the%20country's%20ministers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20are%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iceland's%20Prime%20Minister%20Katr%C3%ADn%20Jakobsd%C3%B3ttir%20is%20seen%20during%20a%20joint%20press%20conference%20in%20the%20Prime%20Ministers%20Office%20in%20Copenhagen%2C%20Denmark%2C%20on%20November%203%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6572fd167a3c8094d5dae85c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKatr%C3%ADn%20Jakobsd%C3%B3ttir%20has%20served%20as%20Iceland's%20prime%20minister%20since%202017.%3Cp%3EMads%20Claus%20Rasmussen%2FRitzau%20Scanpix%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20WEF%20rankings%2C%20%C3%9Eorbergsd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20the%20BSRB%20leader%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20the%20big%20question%20of%20what%20they're%20missing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerhaps%20these%20aren't%20the%20things%20that%20you%20want%20to%20measure%20if%20you%20want%20to%20kind%20of%20describe%20everyday%20life%20of%20people%20in%20Iceland%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20important%20to%20be%20aware%20that%20there%20are%20still%20inequalities%20and%20power%20imbalances%20that%20are%20not%20assessed%20in%20the%20index%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Government%20of%20Iceland%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.government.is%2Ftopics%2Fhuman-rights-and-equality%2Fequality%2Fabout-gender-equality%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esays%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20both%20the%20pay%20gap%20and%20violence%20against%20women%2C%20Iceland%20isn't%20doing%20better%20than%20the%20countries%20it%20compares%20itself%20to%2C%20namely%20the%20Nordics%2C%20%C3%9Eorbergsd%C3%B3ttir%20said.%20Iceland%20ranked%20eighth%20in%20the%20UN%20Development%20Programme's%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhdr.undp.org%2Fdata-center%2Fthematic-composite-indices%2Fgender-inequality-index%23%2Findicies%2FGII%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egender%20inequality%20index%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20behind%20Denmark%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20Sweden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fafallasaga.is%2Fum-rannsoknina%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20more%20than%2032%2C000%20Icelandic%20women%20carried%20out%20across%202018%20and%202019%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Iceland%2C%2040%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they'd%20experienced%20physical%20or%20sexual%20violence%20during%20their%20lifetimes%2C%20and%2032%25%20said%20they'd%20experienced%20sexual%20harassment%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20groups%20of%20women%20are%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20violence%20and%20low%20wages%2C%20including%20foreign-born%20women%2C%20women%20with%20disabilities%2C%20and%20trans%20women%2C%20the%20interviewees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%20feel%20underpaid%20and%20under-appreciated%20at%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIceland%20has%20an%20unadjusted%20gender%20pay%20gap%20of%209.1%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statice.is%2Fpublications%2Fnews-archive%2Fwages-and-income%2Funadjusted-gender-pay-gap-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2022%20data%20from%20Statistics%20Iceland%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20older%20workers%20fare%20significantly%20worse.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.oecd.org%2Fearnwage%2Fgender-wage-gap.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EOECD%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20data%20suggests%20Iceland%20has%20a%20bigger%20gender%20pay%20gap%20than%20the%20three%20Scandinavian%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Denmark%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20Sweden%20%E2%80%93%20as%20well%20as%20Colombia%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20and%20Spain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIceland%20has%20a%20labor-participation%20rate%20of%2061.7%25%20among%20women%20and%2070.5%25%20among%20men%2C%20according%20to%20UN%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhdr.undp.xorg%2Fdata-center%2Fthematic-composite-indices%2Fgender-inequality-index%23%2Findicies%2FGII%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edata%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Women%20work%20on%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhagstofan.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fmedia%2Fpublic%2F2023%2F17783d31-e57c-4109-a0e8-31e7d7c0e853.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eseven%20hours%20a%20week%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20less%20than%20men%20and%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statice.is%2Fpublications%2Fnews-archive%2Flabour-market%2Fpersons-employed-part-time%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enearly%20three%20times%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20likely%20to%20work%20part-time%2C%20meaning%20that%20even%20though%20legislation%20stipulates%20they%20get%20the%20same%20base%20pay%20as%20men%2C%20they%20take%20home%20less%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteinars%20said%20she'd%20been%20treated%20differently%20as%20a%20freelance%20photographer%20to%20her%20male%20counterparts.%20She%20said%20she's%20paid%20significantly%20less%20than%20men%20even%20when%20working%20for%20the%20same%20companies%20and%20gets%20%26quot%3Bput%20in%20very%20stereotypical%20boxes.%26quot%3B%20Though%20she%20specializes%20in%20climbing%20mountains%2C%20skiing%2C%20and%20outdoor%20photography%2C%20some%20companies%20still%20ask%20her%20to%20document%20family%20and%20domestic%20life%20instead%2C%20Steinars%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224321%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%C3%81sa%20Steinars%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6573058258e7c0c29a2aec08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223241%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C3%81sa%20Steinars%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20she%20was%20paid%20significantly%20less%20than%20male%20photographers%20and%20gets%20%26quot%3Bput%20in%20very%20stereotypical%20boxes.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20most%20large%20companies%20in%20Iceland%20are%20dominated%20by%20men%20while%20many%20women%20work%20in%20non-technical%2C%20%26quot%3Bfeminized%26quot%3B%20roles%20like%20HR%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20content%20development%2C%20Alondra%20Silva%20Mu%C3%B1oz%2C%20chair%20of%20WomenTechIceland%2C%20told%20BI.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statice.is%2Fpublications%2Fnews-archive%2Fwages-and-income%2Funadjusted-gender-pay-gap-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EData%20from%20Statistics%20Iceland%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20how%20much%20the%20unadjusted%20gender%20pay%20gap%20varies%20by%20occupation%2C%20with%20a%20gap%20of%2020.5%25%20for%20technicians%20and%20associate%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20are%20deterred%20from%20jobs%20in%20tech%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20safe%20spaces%20to%20address%20issues%20they%20face%20and%20they%20don't%20get%20the%20same%20pay%20and%20opportunities%20as%20men%2C%20Griffin%2C%20the%20WomenTechIceland%20co-founder%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20feel%20appreciated.%20You%20end%20up%20leaving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilva%20Mu%C3%B1oz%20said%20the%20tech%20industry%20wasn't%20doing%20enough%20to%20address%20gender%20inequality%2C%20either.%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20find%20the%20non-profit%20organizations%20taking%20all%20the%20initiative%20to%20work%20on%20these%20issues%2C%20but%20not%20the%20private%20sector%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeaching%2C%20however%2C%20remains%20dominated%20by%20women.%20A%20drop%20in%20salaries%2C%20combined%20with%20changes%20in%20the%201970s%20that%20meant%20schools%20adopted%20a%20%26quot%3Bsofter%20approach%26quot%3B%20and%20focused%20more%20on%20welfare%2C%20meant%20that%20women%20took%20over%20men%20as%20the%20majority%20of%20teachers%2C%20Sigr%C3%BAn%20Birna%20Bj%C3%B6rnsd%C3%B3ttir%20Kaaber%2C%20a%20specialist%20in%20equality%20and%20work%20environment%20at%20the%20Icelandic%20Teachers'%20Union%2C%20and%20Gunnv%C3%B6r%20R%C3%B3sa%20Eyvindard%C3%B3ttir%2C%20a%20gender%20studies%20and%20sociology%20teacher%2C%20told%20BI%20over%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20more%20and%20more%20women%20seeking%20out%20jobs%20within%20male-dominated%20fields%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20same%20cannot%20be%20said%20for%20men%20seeking%20out%20jobs%20within%20female-dominated%20professions%2C%20which%2C%20often%2C%20concern%20pedagogy%20and%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIceland%20is%20no%20'fairyland'%20for%20female%20immigrants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tourism%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20which%20includes%20jobs%20in%20hotels%2C%20cleaning%2C%20and%20restaurants%20%E2%80%94%20has%20big%20problems%20with%20gender%20equality%2C%20Einarsd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20the%20gender-studies%20professor%2C%20said.%20Many%20smaller%20tourism%20companies%20aren't%20properly%20regulated%20and%20offer%20low%20wages%2C%20she%20said%20%E2%80%94%20and%20foreign-born%20workers%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20taking%20on%20these%20poorly-paid%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20Reykjavik%2C%20Iceland%20showing%20mountains%20in%20the%20background%20and%20houses%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657309da7a3c8094d5daea68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222312%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIceland%20has%20a%20booming%20tourism%20industry%20%E2%80%93%20and%20with%20it%20comes%20many%20low-paid%20jobs.%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20have%20a%20very%20big%20problem%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Einarsd%C3%B3ttir%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20immigrant%20women%20were%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap.%20They're%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournal-njmr.org%2Farticles%2F10.33134%2Fnjmr.499%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20vulnerable%20to%20violence%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2020%25%20of%20all%20women%20residing%20in%20Iceland%20were%20born%20overseas%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpx.hagstofa.is%2Fpxen%2Fpxweb%2Fen%2FIbuar%2FIbuar__mannfjoldi__3_bakgrunnur__Faedingarland%2FMAN12103.px%2Ftable%2FtableViewLayout2%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edata%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Statistics%20Iceland.%20Of%20these%20immigrants%2C%20about%20a%20quarter%20were%20born%20in%20Poland%2C%20with%20the%20vast%20majority%20aged%20between%2020%20and%2049.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20both%20an%20immigrant%20and%20a%20woman%2C%20Iceland%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20the%20fairyland%20that's%20being%20promised%20to%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Shruthi%20Basappa%2C%20a%20food%20writer%20and%20co-founder%20of%20architecture%20studio%20SEI%20who%20relocated%20from%20India%20to%20Iceland%2011%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20had%20a%20harder%20time%20being%20a%20professional%20woman%20here%20than%20I%20have%20in%20India%2C%20because%20in%20India%20I'm%20automatically%20an%20architect%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20Iceland%2C%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20what%20room%20I%20am%20in%2C%20even%20as%20a%20professional%2C%20it's%20always%20being%20reduced%20to%20being%20a%20woman%20or%20an%20immigrant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilva%20Mu%C3%B1oz%2C%20the%20WomenTechIceland%20chair%2C%20who%20is%20from%20Chile%2C%20said%20she%20was%20used%20to%20being%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20few%20women%2C%20often%20the%20only%20foreigner%2C%20often%20the%20only%20person%20of%20color%26quot%3B%20in%20professional%20settings.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20the%20responsibility%26quot%3B%20to%20represent%20these%20groups%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%20I'm%20going%20to%20burn%20out.%20I'm%20carrying%20all%20the%20burden.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It's%20very%20important%20not%20to%20celebrate%20that%20you%20are%20the%20best'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Iceland%2C%20there's%20political%20willingness%20to%20introduce%20gender-equality%20laws%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20they're%20not%20always%20effective%2C%26quot%3B%20Einarsd%C3%B3ttir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20many%20interviewees%20told%20BI%20that%20what's%20needed%20is%20more%20of%20a%20mindset%20change%20among%20Icelandic%20men.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20gender-equality%20discourse%20in%20Iceland%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthird-shift-iceland-women-are-tired-of-worrying-gender-equality-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20focused%20on%20the%20concept%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bthird%20shift%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20idea%20that%2C%20on%20top%20of%20going%20to%20work%20and%20physically%20taking%20care%20of%20their%20children%20and%20home%2C%20women%20also%20carry%20the%20mental%20burden%20of%20their%20roles%20as%20wives%2C%20partners%2C%20mothers%2C%20and%20carers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20concern%20politicians%20and%20business%20leaders%20could%20rely%20on%20Iceland's%20reputation%20for%20gender%20equality%20and%20could%20stop%20advancing%20their%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20we%20are%20at%20the%20highest%20rank%20of%20countries%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20a%20good%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Fri%C3%B0riksd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20women's%20travel%20company%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20still%20have%20more%20of%20this%20mountain%20to%20climb%20until%20we%20reach%20the%20top.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEinarsd%C3%B3ttir%20said%20that%20gender-equality%20rankings%20were%20%26quot%3Bvery%20double-edged.%26quot%3B%20Though%20rankings%20motivate%20governments%20to%20top%20the%20lists%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bcan%20play%20arguments%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20those%20who%20can%20say%20that%20this%20is%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sign%20displaying%20the%20logo%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Iceland%20outside%20a%20campus%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6573087058e7c0c29a2aec9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222312%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThorgerdur%20J.%20Einarsd%C3%B3ttir%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20gender%20studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Iceland%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20important%26quot%3B%20to%20not%20take%20gender-equality%20rankings%20too%20seriously.%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20very%20important%20not%20to%20take%20them%20too%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20important%20not%20to%20celebrate%20that%20you%20are%20the%20best%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20dangerous%20because%20it%20brings%20the%20risk%20of%20false%20security%20%5Band%20a%5D%20simplified%20picture%20of%20how%20things%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasappa%2C%20the%20food%20writer%20and%20architect%20from%20India%2C%20said%20she%20thought%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldhappiness.report%2Fed%2F2020%2Fthe-nordic-exceptionalism-what-explains-why-the-nordic-countries-are-constantly-among-the-happiest-in-the-world%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econcept%20of%20Nordic%20exceptionalism%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa