have%20just%20done%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Rather%20than%20have%20to%20go%20through%20the%20wrong%20interpretation%20route%2C%20yeah.%20And%20this%20is%20the%20funny%20thing%20when%20you%20find%20that%20the%20route%20the%20government%20has%20taken%2C%20which%20is%20to%20attempt%20to%20re-interpret%20a%20phrase%20constituent%20assembly%20to%20mean%20legislative%20assembly%2C%20and%20you%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20is%20ultra%20vires%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20root%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20taken.%20The%20logical%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20to%20say%20sorry%2C%20what%20you%E2%80%99ve%20done%20is%20wrong.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20You%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20but%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20say%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20No%2C%20and%20this%20is%20the%20bizarre%20bit.%20Instead%2C%20what%20they%20said%20was%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20another%20way%20of%20doing%20it%20via%20Clause%203%20towards%20requires%20a%20recommendation%20from%20the%20constituent%20assembly%2C%20but%20they%E2%80%99ve%20argued%2C%20and%20I%20think%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20in%20his%20judgment%20argues%20that%20because%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%2C%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20give%20a%20recommendation%20that%20invalidates%20the%20recommendation.%20But%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20invalidate%20the%20power%20of%20the%20president%20to%20act%20without%20any%20recommendation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20now%2C%20but%20for%20that%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20bizarre.%20But%20for%20that%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20use%20Article%20370%20Clause%203%3B%20they%20use%20Article%20370%20Clause%201%20to%20say%20the%20same%20thing%2C%20to%20say%20the%20same%20thing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20But%20then%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20come%20to%20two%20strange%20conclusions.%20First%20of%20all%2C%20it%20seems%20as%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20putting%20arguments%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20mouth%20and%20deeming%20their%20arguments%20to%20be%20correct.%20And%20this%20is%20Kapil%20Sibal%20in%20his%20tweet%20very%20famously%20said%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20his%20tweet%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20had%20little%20to%20do%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20understanding%20of%20Article%20370.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20understanding%20hinged%20upon%20a%20reinterpretation%20of%20the%20constituent%20assembly.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20didn%E2%80%99t%20hinge%20upon%20that%20at%20all%3B%20it%20found%20the%20reinterpretation%20of%20malafide%20and%20ultra%20vires.%20They%20said%20the%20route%20is%20371.%20Yeah%2C%20so%20in%20other%20words%2C%20they%20suggested%20to%20the%20government%20what%20the%20government%20could%20do%20even%20though%20the%20government%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20done%20it.%20And%20then%20presumed%20that%20if%20they%20had%20done%20it%2C%20it%20would%20be%20okay%2C%20therefore%20what%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20done%20is%20okay.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20put%20it%20slightly%20differently.%20The%20case%20of%20the%20government%20was%20dependent%20upon%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20becoming%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly.%20Gee%2C%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20Now%20if%20that%20does%20not%20happen%2C%20then%20the%20case%20falls%20to%20the%20ground.%20What%20the%20government%20also%20seems%20to%20have%20done%20or%20what%20the%20court%20seems%20to%20have%20done%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20if%20the%20government%20argued%20that%2C%20they%20said%20that%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20State%20Assembly%20are%20with%20the%20governor.%20The%20powers%20of%20the%20governor%20are%20with%20the%20president.%20The%20president%20says%2C%20or%20t