n%20set.%20Tomorrow%20or%20the%20day%20after%2C%20if%20the%20government%20were%20to%20choose%2C%20say%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20opposition%20rule%20states%20like%20Bengal%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Kerala%2C%20to%20first%20impose%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20then%20transfer%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20assembly%20to%20Parliament%2C%20and%20if%20Parliament%20decides%20to%20either%20abolish%20the%20state%20altogether%20or%20reduce%20it%20to%20Union%20territory%20status%2C%20what%20the%20president%20has%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Theoretically%2C%20yes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20And%20how%20come%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20didn%E2%80%99t%20realize%20that%20through%20their%20lapse%2C%20allowing%20a%20precedent%20to%20be%20set%20that%20can%20endanger%20Indian%20federalism%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20right.%20It%E2%80%99s%20possible%20that%20Parliament%20does%20this.%20Alright%2C%20take%20any%20particular%20state%20and%20they%20say%20we%E2%80%99re%20converting%20that%20state%20into%20two%20union%20territories%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20challenged%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20says%2C%20well%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20recommendation%20of%20the%20state%20legislature%2C%20and%20even%20if%20there%20is%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20binding%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20binding%20upon%20us.%20So%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20division%20of%20this%20particular%20state%20into%20two%20union%20territories%20is%20okay%2C%20and%20we%20record%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20solicitor%20general%20or%20the%20Attorney%20General%20that%20at%20some%20point%20in%20time%20statehood%20will%20be%20given%20back%20to%20that%20particular%20state.%20Right%2C%20and%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20it%20is%20constitutionally%20valid%20or%20not%2C%20we%20will%20decide%20it%20in%20another%2