5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Linda%20Thomas-Greenfield%2C%20has%20called%20a%20UN%20Security%20Council%20resolution%20on%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgaza-conflict-humanitarian-crisis-worsens-despite-more-aid%2Fa-67759539%5C%22%3EGaza%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0deliveries%20%E2%80%9Ca%20strong%20step%20forward.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20council%20provided%20a%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20among%20a%20sea%20of%20suffering%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThomas-Greenfield%C2%A0said%20the%20resolution%20%E2%80%9Cis%20fully%20supported%20by%20the%20Arab%20group%20that%20provides%20them%20what%20they%20feel%20is%20needed%20to%20get%20humanitarian%20assistance%20on%20the%20ground.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20abstained%20from%20the%20vote%20after%20having%20vetoed%20previous%20resolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWashington%20is%20one%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20most%20important%20allies%20and%20has%20blocked%20attempts%20to%20include%20a%20call%20for%20an%20immediate%20cease-fire%20in%20UN%20Security%20Council%20resolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUAE%20says%20Gaza%20aid%20resolution%20%E2%80%98not%20perfect%2C%E2%80%99%20continues%20calling%20for%20cease-fire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20has%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20calling%20for%20the%C2%A0cessation%20of%20hostilities%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20after%20a%20compromise%20resolution%20on%20aid%20deliveries%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgaza%2Ft-19074241%5C%22%3EGaza%20Strip%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0passed%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20without%20a%20US%20veto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20this%20is%20not%20a%20perfect%20text%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Lana%20Zaki%20Nusseibeh%2C%20the%20UAE%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20never%20tire%20of%20calling%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20cease-fire.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UAE%20sponsored%20the%20resolution.%20Nusseibeh%20said%20it%20%E2%80%9Cresponds%20with%20action%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgaza-conflict-humanitarian-crisis-worsens-despite-more-aid%2Fa-67759539%5C%22%3Edire%20humanitarian%20situation%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20envoy%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Riyad%20Mansour%2C%20called%20the%20resolution%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstep%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMansour%20represents%20the%20Palestinian%20National%20Authority%2C%20which%20is%20based%20in%20Ramallah%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Foccupied-west-bank%2Ft-38397942%5C%22%3Eoccupied%20West%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20is%20led%20by%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Toothless%E2%80%99%20resolution%3A%20Russian%20UN%20ambassador%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Vassily%20Nebenzia%2C%20has%20criticised%20a%20UN%20Security%20Council%20resolution%20on%20Gaza%20aid%20deliveries%20that%20was%20marked%20by%20compromises%20to%20avoid%20a%20US%20veto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Russia%2C%20which%20are%20permanent%20members%20of%20the%20Security%20Council%2C%20abstained%20from%20the%20vote%20but%20did%20not%20veto.%20Washington%20has%20vetoed%20previous%20resolutions%20calling%20for%20an%20immediate%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENebenzia%20called%20the%20resolution%20%E2%80%9Centirely%20toothless.%E2%80%9D%20Russia%20had%20supported%20the%20previous%20two%20motions%20with%20stronger%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20accused%20Washington%20of%20%E2%80%9Cshameful%2C%20cynical%20and%20irresponsible%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20and%20of%20using%20%E2%80%9Cgross%20pressure%2C%20blackmail%20and%20twisting%20arms%E2%80%9D%20to%20chan